Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1 1/2%tsp}, salt, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #plate{}.

Add remaining ginger to same pan over medium-high heat. (TIP: If pan is dry, add another drizzle of olive oil.) Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @apricot jam{2%tablespoon}, @miso sauce concentrate{1}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook until reduced and thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper. Toss broccoli with lime zest and @chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste.

Divide chicken, rice, and broccoli between plates. Top chicken with pan sauce. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> If you want extra heat, top chicken with a pinch of remaining chili flakes.